{"title_page": "Louie Giglio", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Louie Giglio\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = \n| image_size         = 200px\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1958|06|30}}\n| birth_place        = \n| residence          = [[Atlanta, Georgia]]\n| ethnicity          = \n| television         = \n| education          = [[Georgia State University]]<br />[[Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary]]\u2014[[Master of Divinity]]<br />[[Baylor University]]\n| organization       = Passion City Church <br /> [[Passion Conferences]] <br / > sixstepsrecords\n| notable_works      = Not Forsaken <br />Goliath Must Fall <br /> Indescribable: 100 Devotions About God & Science <br /> The Comeback <br /> The Air I Breathe <br /> I am Not But I Know I Am <br /> Waiting Here for You\n| occupation         = Pastor<br />Author <br /> Speaker\n| home_town          = [[Atlanta, Georgia]]\n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = \n| spouse             = Shelley Giglio\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relations          = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| website            = <!-- {{Url|www.louiegiglio.com}} -->\n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Louie Giglio''' (pronounced GIG-leo) is the [[pastor]] of Passion City Church, located in Atlanta, Georgia. He is also a public speaker, author, and the founder of the [[Passion Conferences|Passion Movement]].\n\n==Biography==\nGiglio was born in [[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]] on June 30, 1958.<ref>{{cite web|title=Louie Giglio Artist Profile|url=http://www.newreleasetuesday.com/artistdetail.php?artist_id=1609|publisher=NewsReleaseTuesday|accessdate=January 24, 2013}}</ref> He grew up in the Atlanta suburb of [[Smyrna, Georgia|Smyrna]] and graduated from [[Campbell High School (Georgia)|Campbell High School]].  He later graduated from [[Georgia State University]] and earned a Master of Theology from [[Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary]] in Fort Worth, Texas.<ref name=\"college\">{{Cite web|publisher=Christ Notes|year=2007|title=Louie Giglio Books and Ministry|url=http://www.christnotes.org/_louie-giglio.asp|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080223083952/http://www.christnotes.org/_louie-giglio.asp|archivedate=23 February 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref> Later he went to [[Grace Theological Seminary]] to pursue a Doctor of Ministry degree.<ref name=\"move\" /> After finishing seminary, Giglio and his wife Shelley, whom he married in 1986, began a weekly Bible study called Choice at [[Baylor University]] where he was doing graduate studies. After several years, over 10% of the Baylor student body was attending the weekly gathering, and Giglio's heart for the significance of the \"university moment\" was set.<ref name=\"biblestudy\" >Farias, Andree. (April 25, 2005) [[Christianity Today]]. ''[http://www.christianitytoday.com/music/interviews/2005/louiegiglio-0405.html A Passion for the Christ]'' - Thousands of college students attend Passion worship conferences annually. We talked to the guy behind it all, Louie Giglio, a former campus pastor with a heart on fire for God.</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 1995, Giglio decided to move from their home in Waco, Texas, to Atlanta, Georgia, because of his father's failing health.<ref name=\"move\">Givens, Joshua. (August 13, 2008) [[Associated Content]]. ''Louie Giglio - A Brief Biography on the Renowned Christian Author and Speaker.''</ref> Unfortunately, Louie's father died from a [[brain infection]] and a [[heart attack]] prior to their arrival in Atlanta. However, around that time, during a flight from Texas to Georgia, Louie was inspired to start a national gathering of college students, which would later become [[Passion Conferences]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www1.cbn.com/700club/louie-giglio-heart-behind-passion|title=Louie Giglio: The Heart Behind the Passion|website=CBN.com - The Christian Broadcasting Network|language=en|access-date=2018-03-23}}</ref> The first Passion Conference was held in 1997 in Austin, Texas, with about 2,000 university students in attendance.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/louie-giglio-qa-millennials-may-be-leaving-the-church-but-theyre-walking-toward-christ-part-1-115427/|title=Louie Giglio Q&A: Millennials May Be Leaving the Church But They're Walking Toward Christ (Part 1)|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en}}</ref> Since then, Passion continues to host annual gatherings in the United States and around the world for college students.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> Until the founding of Passion City Church, Giglio was a longtime member of [[North Point Community Church]].\n\nGiglio is the national-bestselling<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/religion/article/73925-may-religion-bestsellers-louie-giglio-breaks-top-four-the-broken-road-takes-1.html|title=May Religion Bestsellers: Louie Giglio Breaks Top Four; 'The Broken Road' Takes #1|work=PublishersWeekly.com|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en}}</ref> author of ''Not Forsaken'', ''Goliath Must Fall, Indescribable: 100 Devotions about God & Science,The Air I Breathe: Worship as a Way of Life'' and ''I Am Not But I Know I Am: Welcome to the Story Of God.'' Giglio's latest release, ''Not Forsaken'', debuted at number 3 on the Publishers Weekly Trade Paper Frontlist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhpublishinggroup.com/bestselling-author-and-passion-movement-founder-louie-giglios-new-booknot-forsaken-hits-no-3-on-the-publishers-weekly-bestseller-list/|title=Bestselling author and Passion movement founder Louie Giglio's new book \"Not Forsaken\" hits No. 3 on the Publishers Weekly bestseller list|date=2019-05-20|website=B&H Publishing|language=en|access-date=2019-06-13}}</ref>, and ranked number 6 on the May 2019 Religion Nonfiction bestsellers list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/religion/article/80429-may-religion-bestsellers-the-rational-bible-is-back-richard-paul-evans-tops.html|title=May Religion Bestsellers: The Rational Bible is Back; Richard Paul Evans Tops|website=PublishersWeekly.com|language=en|access-date=2019-06-13}}</ref> His previous trade release, ''Goliath Must Fall,'' made the Publishers Weekly bestseller list in May 2017 <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/religion/article/73925-may-religion-bestsellers-louie-giglio-breaks-top-four-the-broken-road-takes-1.html|title=May Religion Bestsellers: Louie Giglio Breaks Top Four|date=8 June 2017|publisher=Publishers Weekly}}</ref> and was #31 in the list of the top 100 bestselling Christian books of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gospelebooks.net/ecpa-bestsellers-2017-books-1-50|title=ECPA Bestsellers 2017 Books|publisher=Evangelical Christian Publishers Association (ECPA)|accessdate=28 February 2018}}</ref> His talks \"Indescribable\" and \"How Great Is Our God\" have been viewed by churches and individuals around the world. The \"[[Laminin]]\" clip from his message \"How Great Is Our God\" has been viewed over 3 million times on YouTube.<ref>{{YouTube|_e4zgJXPpI4}}{{dead link|date=January 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Passion Conferences==\n{{Main|Passion Conferences}}\nSince 1995, the Passion Movement has hosted close to a million university students at events ranging from the first Passion Conference in Austin, Texas, in January 1997 which 2,000 people attended to \"OneDay 2000\", a gathering of 40,000 students for prayer and worship outside Memphis, Tennessee, to the seventeen-city Passion World Tour of 2008.<ref>Hansen, Collin. (March 23, 2007)  [[Christianity Today]]. ''[http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2007/april/20.29.html Passion Takes It Higher]'' - The most influential annual gathering of young evangelicals plans to go global.</ref> Passion has hosted local campus events at leading universities in The U.S., as well as larger regional and national events in cities like Seattle, Los Angeles, Boston, Chicago, Dallas, Minneapolis and Washington, D.C.\n\nNotably, in January 2017, more than 55,000 students gathered for Passion 2017 in Atlanta's [[Georgia Dome]] for one of the largest Jesus-focused events in its history,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.louiegiglio.com/about/|title=About \u2013 Louie Giglio|website=www.louiegiglio.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-23}}</ref> and one of the last events to be held in the Georgia Dome prior to its November 2017 implosion.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/11/20/sport/georgia-dome-imploded/index.html|title=Georgia Dome imploded after 25 years of use|first=Jill |last=Martin|work=CNN|access-date=2018-03-23}}</ref> Each year, Passion Conference attendees are encouraged to give generously toward Christian outreach around the world: raising $785,000 to build a Syrian Hospital in 2016<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://college.usatoday.com/2016/01/05/hristian-conference-raise-money-to-build-syrian-hospital/|title=Students at Christian conference raise $785,000 to build Syrian hospital|date=2016-01-05|work=USA TODAY College|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en-US}}</ref> and sponsoring 7,000 at-risk children through Compassion International in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/news/2017/january/passion-conference-students-child-sponsorship-compassion.html|title=Passion Students Sponsor Every Compassion Child in Four Countries|work=News & Reporting|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en}}</ref>\n\nAs a part of the Passion movement, Giglio also founded sixstepsrecords, a record company that works in partnership with [[Sparrow Records]] and is a subsidiary of Passion Conferences. This label is home to artists [[Crowder (musician)|Crowder]], Sean Curran<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://freeccm.com/2019/02/18/news-passion-drops-empowering-step-into-the-light-featuring-sean-curran/|title=News: Passion Drops Empowering \"Step Into The Light\" Featuring Sean Curran {{!}} Freeccm.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-13}}</ref>, [[Kristian Stanfill]], and Passion.<ref>Geil, Mark. (November 17, 2008) [[Christianity Today]]. ''[http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/music/news/2008/sixsteprecords.html What's in a Label?: sixstepsrecords]'' - Learn how a tiny homespun record label focused solely on worship became one of the most successful in the music business today, fueled by music from the likes of Chris Tomlin and David Crowder.</ref> In 2008, Giglio, with the help of Chris Tomlin, founded [[megachurch]] Passion City Church, a branch of Passion Conferences, in Atlanta, GA.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://john.do/chris-tomlin-leaving-austin-stone/|title=Chris Tomlin leaving Austin Stone!!! \u2013 john saddington|date=May 11, 2008|work=john saddington|access-date=November 19, 2018}}</ref> Passion City Church would later expand to [[Cumberland, Georgia|Cumberland]], Georgia<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ajc.com/news/local/passion-city-church-approved-for-cumberland-expansion/MkwsuA84kFwKlSmqoSQOrL/|title=Passion City Church approved for Cumberland expansion|work=ajc|access-date=November 19, 2018}}</ref> and [[Washington, D.C.]] in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://passioncitychurch.com/dc/|title=D.C.|work=Passion City Church|access-date=November 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Writings==\n* {{cite book |author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask= |title=The Air I Breathe: [worship as a way of life] |location=Sisters, OR |publisher=Multnomah |date=2003 |isbn=9781590526705 |oclc=71826079 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781590526705 }}\n* {{cite book|author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask=3 |title=I Am Not But I Know I Am: Welcome to the Story of God |location=Sisters, OR |publisher=Multnomah |date=2005 |isbn=9781590522752 |oclc=57531626 }}\n* {{cite book |author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask=3 |title=Wired: For a Life of Worship; Journey: 30 day worship |location=Sisters, OR |publisher=Multnomah |date=2006 |isbn=9781590525838 |oclc=62084261 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/wiredforlifeofwo00gigl }} - a version of ''The Air I Breathe''\n* {{cite book|author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Redman |author2-first=Matt |author2-link=Matt Redman |title=Indescribable: encountering the glory of God in the beauty of the universe |location=Colorado Springs, CO |publisher=David C. Cook |date=2011 |isbn=9780781406031 |oclc=759519752 }}\n* {{cite book|author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask=3 |author2-last=Moore |author2-first=Beth |author2-link=Beth Moore |author3-last=Caine |author3-first=Christine |author3-link=Christine Caine |author4-last=Piper |author4-first=John |author4-link=John Piper (theologian) |author5-last=Smith |author5-first=Judah |author5-link=Judah Smith |author6-last=Chan |author6-first=Francis |author6-link=Francis Chan |title=Passion: the bright light of glory |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=Thomas Nelson |date=2014 |isbn=9780529110114 |oclc=871177000 }}\n* {{cite book|author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask=3 |title=The Comeback: it's not too late and you're never too far |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=Thomas Nelson |date=2015 |isbn=9780718097134 |oclc=962835105 }}\n* {{cite book|author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask=3 |title=Goliath Must Fall: Winning the Battle Against Your Giants |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=Thomas Nelson |date=2017 |isbn=9780718088866 |oclc=962835106 }}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thomasnelson.com/goliath-must-fall |title=Goliath Must Fall |accessdate=June 14, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180204105843/http://www.thomasnelson.com/goliath-must-fall |archive-date=February 4, 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* {{cite book|author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask=3 |title=Indescribable: 100 Devotions About God & Science |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=Thomas Nelson |date=2017 |isbn=9780718086107 |oclc=979564065 }}\n* {{cite book|author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask=3 |title=Not Forsaken: Finding Freedom as Sons & Daughters of a Perfect Father |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=B&H Books |date=2019 |isbn=9781535956956 |oclc=1081385221 }}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bhpublishinggroup.com/bestselling-author-and-passion-founder-louie-giglio-releases-new-book-not-forsaken-more-passion-resources-to-come-this-year/|title=Bestselling author and Passion founder Louie Giglio Releases new book \"Not Forsaken,\" More Passion resources to come this year|date=2019-02-05|website=B&H Publishing|language=en|access-date=2019-06-13}}</ref>\n* {{cite book|author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask=3 |title=How Great Is Our God: 100 Indescribable Devotions About God and Science |location=Nashville, TN |publisher=Tommy Nelson |date=2019 |isbn=9781400217212 |oclc=1104859319 }}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.christianpost.com/books/louie-giglios-new-childrens-devotional-hopes-to-bridge-the-divide-between-god-and-science.html|title=Louie Giglio's new children's devotional hopes to bridge the divide between God and science|date=2019-12-09|website=Christian Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.passioncitychurch.com Passion City Church]\n* [http://www.268generation.com 268generation] - Web site for Passion Conferences\n* [http://www.sixstepsrecords.com sixstepsrecords] - Home of Crowder, Sean Curran, Kristian Stanfill, and Passion.\n* [https://www.louiegiglio.com/ louiegiglio.com] - Louie Giglio official website\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Giglio, Louie}}\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Protestant ministers and clergy]]\n[[Category:Christian writers]]\n[[Category:Baylor University alumni]]\n[[Category:Southern Baptists]]\n[[Category:Georgia State University alumni]]\n[[Category:Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary alumni]]\n[[Category:Grace Theological Seminary alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Louie Giglio\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = \n| image_size         = 200px\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1958|06|30}}\n| birth_place        = \n| residence          = [[Atlanta, Georgia]]\n| ethnicity          = \n| television         = \n| education          = [[Georgia State University]]<br />[[Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary]]\u2014[[Master of Divinity]]<br />[[Baylor University]]\n| organization       = Passion City Church <br /> [[Passion Conferences]] <br / > sixstepsrecords\n| notable_works      = Not Forsaken <br />Goliath Must Fall <br /> Indescribable: 100 Devotions About God & Science <br /> The Comeback <br /> The Air I Breathe <br /> I am Not But I Know I Am <br /> Waiting Here for You\n| occupation         = Pastor<br />Author <br /> Speaker\n| home_town          = [[Atlanta, Georgia]]\n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = \n| spouse             = Shelley Giglio\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relations          = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| website            = <!-- {{Url|www.louiegiglio.com}} -->\n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Louie Giglio''' (pronounced GIG-leo) is the [[pastor]] of Passion City Church, located in Atlanta, Georgia. He is also a public speaker, author, and the founder of the [[Passion Conferences|Passion Movement]].\n\n==Biography==\nGiglio was born in [[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]] on June 30, 1958.<ref>{{cite web|title=Louie Giglio Artist Profile|url=http://www.newreleasetuesday.com/artistdetail.php?artist_id=1609|publisher=NewsReleaseTuesday|accessdate=January 24, 2013}}</ref> He grew up in the Atlanta suburb of [[Smyrna, Georgia|Smyrna]] and graduated from [[Campbell High School (Georgia)|Campbell High School]].  He later graduated from [[Georgia State University]] and earned a Master of Theology from [[Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary]] in Fort Worth, Texas.<ref name=\"college\">{{Cite web|publisher=Christ Notes|year=2007|title=Louie Giglio Books and Ministry|url=http://www.christnotes.org/_louie-giglio.asp|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080223083952/http://www.christnotes.org/_louie-giglio.asp|archivedate=23 February 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref> Later he went to [[Grace Theological Seminary]] to pursue a Doctor of Ministry degree.<ref name=\"move\" /> After finishing seminary, Giglio and his wife Shelley, whom he married in 1986, began a weekly Bible study called Choice at [[Baylor University]] where he was doing graduate studies. After several years, over 10% of the Baylor student body was attending the weekly gathering, and Giglio's heart for the significance of the \"university moment\" was set.<ref name=\"biblestudy\" >Farias, Andree. (April 25, 2005) [[Christianity Today]]. ''[http://www.christianitytoday.com/music/interviews/2005/louiegiglio-0405.html A Passion for the Christ]'' - Thousands of college students attend Passion worship conferences annually. We talked to the guy behind it all, Louie Giglio, a former campus pastor with a heart on fire for God.</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 1995, Giglio decided to move from their home in Waco, Texas, to Atlanta, Georgia, because of his father's failing health.<ref name=\"move\">Givens, Joshua. (August 13, 2008) [[Associated Content]]. ''Louie Giglio - A Brief Biography on the Renowned Christian Author and Speaker.''</ref> Unfortunately, Louie's father died from a [[brain infection]] and a [[heart attack]] prior to their arrival in Atlanta. However, around that time, during a flight from Texas to Georgia, Louie was inspired to start a national gathering of college students, which would later become [[Passion Conferences]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www1.cbn.com/700club/louie-giglio-heart-behind-passion|title=Louie Giglio: The Heart Behind the Passion|website=CBN.com - The Christian Broadcasting Network|language=en|access-date=2018-03-23}}</ref> The first Passion Conference was held in 1997 in Austin, Texas, with about 2,000 university students in attendance.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/louie-giglio-qa-millennials-may-be-leaving-the-church-but-theyre-walking-toward-christ-part-1-115427/|title=Louie Giglio Q&A: Millennials May Be Leaving the Church But They're Walking Toward Christ (Part 1)|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en}}</ref> Since then, Passion continues to host annual gatherings in the United States and around the world for college students.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> Until the founding of Passion City Church, Giglio was a longtime member of [[North Point Community Church]].\n\nGiglio is the national-bestselling<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/religion/article/73925-may-religion-bestsellers-louie-giglio-breaks-top-four-the-broken-road-takes-1.html|title=May Religion Bestsellers: Louie Giglio Breaks Top Four; 'The Broken Road' Takes #1|work=PublishersWeekly.com|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en}}</ref> author of ''Not Forsaken'', ''Goliath Must Fall, Indescribable: 100 Devotions about God & Science,The Air I Breathe: Worship as a Way of Life'' and ''I Am Not But I Know I Am: Welcome to the Story Of God.'' Giglio's latest release, ''Not Forsaken'', debuted at number 3 on the Publishers Weekly Trade Paper Frontlist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhpublishinggroup.com/bestselling-author-and-passion-movement-founder-louie-giglios-new-booknot-forsaken-hits-no-3-on-the-publishers-weekly-bestseller-list/|title=Bestselling author and Passion movement founder Louie Giglio's new book \"Not Forsaken\" hits No. 3 on the Publishers Weekly bestseller list|date=2019-05-20|website=B&H Publishing|language=en|access-date=2019-06-13}}</ref>, and ranked number 6 on the May 2019 Religion Nonfiction bestsellers list<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/religion/article/80429-may-religion-bestsellers-the-rational-bible-is-back-richard-paul-evans-tops.html|title=May Religion Bestsellers: The Rational Bible is Back; Richard Paul Evans Tops|website=PublishersWeekly.com|language=en|access-date=2019-06-13}}</ref>. His previous trade release, ''Goliath Must Fall,'' made the Publishers Weekly bestseller list in May 2017 <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/religion/article/73925-may-religion-bestsellers-louie-giglio-breaks-top-four-the-broken-road-takes-1.html|title=May Religion Bestsellers: Louie Giglio Breaks Top Four|date=8 June 2017|publisher=Publishers Weekly}}</ref> and was #31 in the list of the top 100 bestselling Christian books of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gospelebooks.net/ecpa-bestsellers-2017-books-1-50|title=ECPA Bestsellers 2017 Books|publisher=Evangelical Christian Publishers Association (ECPA)|accessdate=28 February 2018}}</ref> His talks \"Indescribable\" and \"How Great Is Our God\" have been viewed by churches and individuals around the world. The \"[[Laminin]]\" clip from his message \"How Great Is Our God\" has been viewed over 3 million times on YouTube.<ref>{{YouTube|_e4zgJXPpI4}}{{dead link|date=January 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Passion Conferences==\n{{Main|Passion Conferences}}\nSince 1995, the Passion Movement has hosted close to a million university students at events ranging from the first Passion Conference in Austin, Texas, in January 1997 which 2,000 people attended to \"OneDay 2000\", a gathering of 40,000 students for prayer and worship outside Memphis, Tennessee, to the seventeen-city Passion World Tour of 2008.<ref>Hansen, Collin. (March 23, 2007)  [[Christianity Today]]. ''[http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2007/april/20.29.html Passion Takes It Higher]'' - The most influential annual gathering of young evangelicals plans to go global.</ref> Passion has hosted local campus events at leading universities in The U.S., as well as larger regional and national events in cities like Seattle, Los Angeles, Boston, Chicago, Dallas, Minneapolis and Washington, D.C.\n\nNotably, in January 2017, more than 55,000 students gathered for Passion 2017 in Atlanta's [[Georgia Dome]] for one of the largest Jesus-focused events in its history,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.louiegiglio.com/about/|title=About \u2013 Louie Giglio|website=www.louiegiglio.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-23}}</ref> and one of the last events to be held in the Georgia Dome prior to its November 2017 implosion.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/11/20/sport/georgia-dome-imploded/index.html|title=Georgia Dome imploded after 25 years of use|first=Jill |last=Martin|work=CNN|access-date=2018-03-23}}</ref> Each year, Passion Conference attendees are encouraged to give generously toward Christian outreach around the world: raising $785,000 to build a Syrian Hospital in 2016<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://college.usatoday.com/2016/01/05/hristian-conference-raise-money-to-build-syrian-hospital/|title=Students at Christian conference raise $785,000 to build Syrian hospital|date=2016-01-05|work=USA TODAY College|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en-US}}</ref> and sponsoring 7,000 at-risk children through Compassion International in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/news/2017/january/passion-conference-students-child-sponsorship-compassion.html|title=Passion Students Sponsor Every Compassion Child in Four Countries|work=News & Reporting|access-date=2018-03-23|language=en}}</ref>\n\nAs a part of the Passion movement, Giglio also founded sixstepsrecords, a record company that works in partnership with [[Sparrow Records]] and is a subsidiary of Passion Conferences. This label is home to artists [[Crowder (musician)|Crowder]], Sean Curran<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://freeccm.com/2019/02/18/news-passion-drops-empowering-step-into-the-light-featuring-sean-curran/|title=News: Passion Drops Empowering \"Step Into The Light\" Featuring Sean Curran {{!}} Freeccm.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-13}}</ref>, [[Kristian Stanfill]], and Passion.<ref>Geil, Mark. (November 17, 2008) [[Christianity Today]]. ''[http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/music/news/2008/sixsteprecords.html What's in a Label?: sixstepsrecords]'' - Learn how a tiny homespun record label focused solely on worship became one of the most successful in the music business today, fueled by music from the likes of Chris Tomlin and David Crowder.</ref> In 2008, Giglio, with the help of Chris Tomlin, founded [[megachurch]] Passion City Church, a branch of Passion Conferences, in Atlanta, GA.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://john.do/chris-tomlin-leaving-austin-stone/|title=Chris Tomlin leaving Austin Stone!!! \u2013 john saddington|date=May 11, 2008|work=john saddington|access-date=November 19, 2018}}</ref> Passion City Church would later expand to [[Cumberland, Georgia|Cumberland]], Georgia<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ajc.com/news/local/passion-city-church-approved-for-cumberland-expansion/MkwsuA84kFwKlSmqoSQOrL/|title=Passion City Church approved for Cumberland expansion|work=ajc|access-date=November 19, 2018}}</ref> and [[Washington, D.C.]] in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://passioncitychurch.com/dc/|title=D.C.|work=Passion City Church|access-date=November 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Writings==\n* {{cite book |author1-last=Giglio |author1-first=Louie |author1-mask= |title=The Air I Breathe: [worship as a way of life] |location=Sisters, OR |publisher=Multnomah |date=2003 |isbn=9781590526705 |oclc=71826079 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781590526705 }}\n* {{cite book|author1-